<normalizedToken id="BFB8CD8C71A76DE69681BA35C66D9374" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide hyphae, slightly yellowish to brownish hyaline in KOH or NH4OH. Pileipellis a tangled trichoderm to tomentum at places, 70-110 
<normalizedToken id="3FC033BB110EADE18C8187B32385CB63" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
thick, composed of moderately interwoven thin-walled hyphae; terminal cells 12-48 
<normalizedToken id="3079BBE13641A5C8E635ED934C25B924" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-7 
<normalizedToken id="F36EDD3DFC5DD1A7794068B55E40BCF3" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
mostly slightly sinuate, cylindrical to irregular with rounded apex, at places clavate to elongated clavate terminal cells 18-33 
<normalizedToken id="C863F7B4EBF29B97A958F36CEA1CEA2D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
